"v.先发制人，预先阻止 【英】 v. 先发制人，预先阻止( to prevent or hinder by doing something ahead of time; prevent) 【考】 反义词：precipitate (促成); abet(支持) 【记】 fore(前面)+stall(停 止)→预先阻止 【同】 参考：install(安置) 【例】 She forestalled their attempt. v. (用先发制人的办法)预先阻止; 比...先采取行动 = anticipate 【源】原指: 垄断市场预先囤积、阻止正常销售从而擡高价格 【记】fore前, stall(n 货摊v 使停止; 迟延)－预先阻止 【参】install(vt 安装; 安置; 使就职) 【反】precipitated(vt 猛抛; 促成; 使沉淀); abet(vt 教唆; 支持) 【记】fore 前 + stall 货摊，提前出摊，抢占地方→先发制人，阻止他人 forestall (v.)  late 14c. (implied in forestalling), ""to lie in wait for;"" also ""to intercept goods before they reach public markets and buy them privately"" (formerly a crime; mid-14c. in this sense in Anglo-French), from Old English noun foresteall ""intervention, hindrance (of justice); an ambush, a waylaying,"" literally ""a standing before (someone),"" from fore- ""before"" + steall ""standing position"" (see stall (n.1)). Modern sense of ""to anticipate and delay"" is from 1580s. Related: Forestalled; forestalling."
